pull_request.title: Use OpenSSL for AES when available
pull_request.body: Note that this version has the `aes_ni.c` file still in there, but isn't actually compiling it ever in to the library, so AES is only either the plain C implementation or the OpenSSL optimized implementation.  Is it worth having our own local NI implementation, or just always relying on the OpenSSL one?
